<snip>

 Some attempts are made in Haskell in order to return more comprehensive
error reports for beginners. Helium may be a good source of inspiration
for a "beginners-only" ocaml compiler:
 http://www.cs.uu.nl/~afie/helium/
 IMHO, syntactic aspects could be handled by an instance of ocamlp4. But
what about the rest ?

